00:25:03.100 --> 00:25:06.580 align:middle line:84%
that unites 17,000 scientists
from across the world,

00:25:06.580 --> 00:25:09.730 align:middle line:84%
is presenting the findings
of its latest study.

00:25:09.730 --> 00:25:13.300 align:middle line:84%
It is a unique event that is
broadcast to the United States

00:25:13.300 --> 00:25:14.360 align:middle line:90%
and Europe.

00:25:14.360 --> 00:25:16.330 align:middle line:84%
The researchers
are today warning

00:25:16.330 --> 00:25:19.840 align:middle line:84%
about the effect of chemical
pollutants on children's brains

00:25:19.840 --> 00:25:24.680 align:middle line:90%
and of autism in particular.

00:25:24.680 --> 00:25:29.050 align:middle line:84%
>> So we produced a study that
demonstrates that two chemicals

00:25:29.050 --> 00:25:34.270 align:middle line:84%
produce autistic-like behaviors
in an animal model of autism.

00:25:34.270 --> 00:25:37.600 align:middle line:84%
These are extremely
important implications.

00:25:37.600 --> 00:25:43.030 align:middle line:84%
>> We have all of the mothers
behind us when we say we must

00:25:43.030 --> 00:25:45.220 align:middle line:84%
protect the next
generation's brains.

00:25:45.220 --> 00:25:46.900 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:25:46.900 --> 00:25:49.810 align:middle line:84%
>> Chemical products are
responsible for autism?

00:25:49.810 --> 00:25:51.910 align:middle line:84%
Before he leaves to
return to Harvard,

00:25:51.910 --> 00:25:54.970 align:middle line:84%
we corner this research
scientist to find out more.

00:25:54.970 --> 00:26:00.550 align:middle line:84%
>> Right now, we have a total of
12 chemicals on the list where

00:26:00.550 --> 00:26:06.010 align:middle line:84%
we are convinced that those
chemicals actually harm

00:26:06.010 --> 00:26:10.220 align:middle line:84%
children in regard to
their brain development.

00:26:10.220 --> 00:26:14.650 align:middle line:84%
We have also added some
