county courthouse.

00:50:14.480 --> 00:50:17.720 align:middle line:84%
The hearing was due to
start in just a few minutes.

00:50:17.720 --> 00:50:20.150 align:middle line:84%
It's impossible to film
inside the building.

00:50:20.150 --> 00:50:22.940 align:middle line:84%
Two hours later and
against all expectations,

00:50:22.940 --> 00:50:25.880 align:middle line:84%
the judges ruled in favor
of the multinationals

00:50:25.880 --> 00:50:27.320 align:middle line:90%
and invalidated the law.

00:50:27.320 --> 00:50:30.630 align:middle line:90%


00:50:30.630 --> 00:50:33.030 align:middle line:84%
The eight lawyers from
the pesticide industry

00:50:33.030 --> 00:50:34.440 align:middle line:90%
left the courthouse.

00:50:34.440 --> 00:50:36.630 align:middle line:84%
Marjorie Bronster
led the appeal.

00:50:36.630 --> 00:50:38.760 align:middle line:84%
>> --from friends of
the French National TV.

00:50:38.760 --> 00:50:41.740 align:middle line:84%
Now for this-- it's
a lei from Maui.

00:50:41.740 --> 00:50:42.540 align:middle line:90%
Can I offer you?

00:50:42.540 --> 00:50:42.740 align:middle line:90%
>> Oh, really?

00:50:42.740 --> 00:50:43.480 align:middle line:90%
Yes, you may.

00:50:43.480 --> 00:50:43.730 align:middle line:90%
>> Yeah.

00:50:43.730 --> 00:50:45.000 align:middle line:90%
OK, how would you--

00:50:45.000 --> 00:50:46.590 align:middle line:90%
put it like this, OK.

00:50:46.590 --> 00:50:51.298 align:middle line:84%
We took the samples from
the GMO fields down in Maui.

00:50:51.298 --> 00:50:53.090 align:middle line:84%
These flowers actually
are from GMO fields.

00:50:53.090 --> 00:50:56.430 align:middle line:84%
They might be full of
pesticides still though.

00:50:56.430 --> 00:51:00.010 align:middle line:84%
I mean, I know what
you think about that.

00:51:00.010 --> 00:51:01.770 align:middle line:84%
How do you-- what do
you think of the fact

00:51:01.770 --> 00:51:05.610 align:middle line:84%
that a democratic
process being challenged

00:51:05.610 --> 00:51:09.180 align:middle line:84%
by big companies like the one
you represent, Dow, [INAUDIBLE]

00:51:09.180 --> 00:51:10.020 align:middle line:90%
or even Monsanto?

00:51:10.020 --> 00:51:11.103 align:middle line:90%
What do you think of that?

00:51:11.103 --> 00:51:14.070 align:middle line:84%
>> Well, I represent a lot
of parties in this case.

00:51:14.070 --> 00:51:15.750 align:middle line:84%
Not all of them are
large companies.

00:51:15.750 --> 00:51:17.940 align:middle line:84%
But I will tell you
that the question

00:51:17.940 --> 00:51:20.970 align:middle line:84%
that the court had
to address is who

00:51:20.970 --> 00:51:22.980 align:middle line:90%
has the authority to regulate.

00:51:22.980 --> 00:51:24.630 align:middle line:84%
The court is not
going to be addressing

00:51:24.630 --> 00:51:28.510 align:middle line:84%
the question of whether the
pesticides are good or bad.

00:51:28.510 --> 00:51:31.560 align:middle line:84%
It's really a question as
to whether the county has

00:51:31.560 --> 00:51:34.500 align:middle line:84%
the right to step in and
regulate in this area.

00:51:34.500 --> 00:51:40.140 align:middle line:84%
And our position is simply
that this is not a county area.

00:51:40.140 --> 00:51:43.200 align:middle line:84%
It is for the state or the
federal government to regulate,

00:51:43.200 --> 00:51:44.960 align:middle line:84%
and they have been
regulating this area.

00:51:44.960 --> 00:51:47.460 align:middle line:84%
>> Do you think the people from
Maui did not vote correctly?

00:51:47.460 --> 00:51:49.070 align:middle line:90%
>> Thank you.

00:51:49.070 --> 00:51:49.870 align:middle line:90%
>> I mean--

00:51:49.870 --> 00:51:51.500 align:middle line:84%
I'm sorry to insist, because
we've-- you know we traveled

00:51:51.500 --> 00:51:52.450 align:middle line:90%
a long way to come here.

00:51:52.450 --> 00:51:54.880 align:middle line:84%
So do you think the people from
Maui did not vote correctly?

00:51:54.880 --> 00:51:55.680 align:middle line:90%
What do you think?

00:51:55.680 --> 00:52:00.420 align:middle line:84%
>> As I mentioned in court and
as I think the question is,

00:52:00.420 --> 00:52:03.120 align:middle line:84%
do the voters have the right
to regulate in this area?

00:52:03.120 --> 00:52:04.830 align:middle line:90%
We believe that they do not.

00:52:04.830 --> 00:52:07.680 align:middle line:84%
>> What kind of message do you
think that sends to the people

00:52:07.680 --> 00:52:11.310 align:middle line:84%
that believe that votes
can change things?

00:52:11.310 --> 00:52:13.470 align:middle line:90%
What do you think of that?

00:52:13.470 --> 00:52:17.070 align:middle line:84%
>> Certainly, the initiative
process is appropriate

00:52:17.070 --> 00:52:19.470 align:middle line:84%
in certain areas, but we do
not believe that this is one

00:52:19.470 --> 00:52:20.270 align:middle line:90%
of them.

00:52:20.270 --> 00:52:20.620 align:middle line:90%
>> Right.

00:52:20.620 --> 00:52:22.412 align:middle line:84%
Very last question,
Miss Bronster, and I'll

00:52:22.412 --> 00:52:23.410 align:middle line:90%
leave you alone.

00:52:23.410 --> 00:52:26.780 align:middle line:84%
Do you personally believe
that the pesticides used

00:52:26.780 --> 00:52:30.440 align:middle line:84%
on Maui, on Kauai and large
islands-- some of there

00:52:30.440 --> 00:52:33.300 align:middle line:84%
are neurotoxic, some of there
are carcinogenic, some of them

00:52:33.300 --> 00:52:35.090 align:middle line:90%
are toxic for the fetus.

00:52:35.090 --> 00:52:37.650 align:middle line:84%
Do you think this is
good for a community?

00:52:37.650 --> 00:52:39.850 align:middle line:84%
Do you think for the
children it's good as well?

00:52:39.850 --> 00:52:42.480 align:middle line:84%
>> As I mentioned, that's
not what this case is about,

00:52:42.480 --> 00:52:43.890 align:middle line:84%
and I'm not going
to get into it.

00:52:43.890 --> 00:52:44.070 align:middle line:90%
Thank you.

00:52:44.070 --> 00:52:46.153 align:middle line:84%
>> As a human being, what
do you think about that?

00:52:46.153 --> 00:52:50.700 align:middle line:90%


00:52:50.700 --> 00:52:52.490 align:middle line:84%
>> Meanwhile in front
of the courthouse,

00:52:52.490 --> 00:52:55.050 align:middle line:84%
the island's inhabitants who
had supported the law were still

00:52:55.050 --> 00:52:55.850 align:middle line:90%
reeling.

00:52:55.850 --> 00:52:59.880 align:middle line:90%


00:52:59.880 --> 00:53:01.370 align:middle line:90%
>> It's like saying--

00:53:01.370 --> 00:53:03.830 align:middle line:90%
it's saying we don't count.

00:53:03.830 --> 00:53:08.690 align:middle line:84%
What it's saying is
that corporations, yeah,

00:53:08.690 --> 00:53:14.060 align:middle line:84%
have more importance in their
world than we the people

00:53:14.060 --> 00:53:17.300 align:middle line:90%
and the children, yeah?

00:53:17.300 --> 00:53:20.180 align:middle line:84%
We go through this
belief of having

00:53:20.180 --> 00:53:23.480 align:middle line:84%
the right to express
ourselves and vote,

00:53:23.480 --> 00:53:24.950 align:middle line:90%
and we have done that.

00:53:24.950 --> 00:53:29.612 align:middle line:84%
And we were victorious, and
then they holed everything up.

00:53:29.612 --> 00:53:31.260 align:middle line:90%
[MUSIC PLAYING]

00:53:31.260 --> 00:53:34.970 align:middle line:84%
>> In Hawaii, in the
great democracy game,

00:53:34.970 --> 00:53:37.950 align:middle line:84%
the chemical industry
is the winner.

00:53:37.950 --> 00:53:40.080 align:middle line:84%
As our investigation
drew to a close,

00:53:40.080 --> 00:53:41.940 align:middle line:84%
we wondered if our
children would end up

00:53:41.940 --> 00:53:44.550 align:middle line:84%
having to live like
this, protected

00:53:44.550 --> 00:53:46.770 align:middle line:90%
against their own environment.

00:53:46.770 --> 00:53:49.410 align:middle line:84%
At least there was
some good news, though.

00:53:49.410 --> 00:53:53.010 align:middle line:84%
Amongst the 50 Bayer products
classified as dangerous,

00:53:53.010 --> 00:53:55.380 align:middle line:84%
six were withdrawn
from the French market.

00:53:55.380 --> 00:53:58.820 align:middle line:90%


00:53:58.820 --> 00:54:02.750 align:middle line:84%
Chlorpyrifos, the pesticide
that is neurotoxic to children,

00:54:02.750 --> 00:54:05.450 align:middle line:84%
is due to be banned in the
United States and France

00:54:05.450 --> 00:54:07.190 align:middle line:90%
in the coming months.

00:54:07.190 --> 00:54:10.400 align:middle line:84%
In French schools located
close to application zones,

00:54:10.400 --> 00:54:14.120 align:middle line:84%
the installation of
antipesticide walls or nets

00:54:14.120 --> 00:54:16.820 align:middle line:90%
has begun around the buildings.

00:54:16.820 --> 00:54:19.220 align:middle line:84%
It's scant protection,
but maybe it

00:54:19.220 --> 00:54:21.400 align:middle line:84%
is the start of a
general awareness.

00:54:21.400 --> 00:54:24.460 align:middle line:90%


00:54:24.460 --> 00:54:25.260 align:middle line:90%
